Fontaines D.C. is going on tour! and their new album is out August 23rd Sept 20, 2024 Seattle @ Showbox SoDo Sept 21, 2024 Portland, OR @ Roseland Theater Sept 22, 2024 Vancouver, BC @ Commodore Ballroom Sept 24, 2024 San Francisco, CA @ The Warfield https://fontainesdc.com/pages/romance-north-american-tour-2024 06/22/2024 01:50 PM

DJ: Morgan The Understanding is the second studio album by Norwegian electronic music duo Röyksopp. It was released on this date in 2005! 06/22/2024 01:48 PM

DJ: Morgan Abstract Crimewave, formerly known as Smile (hmm, I wonder why they changed their name?), have announced their new album The Longest Night which drops October 4th. Peter Bjorn And John’s Björn Yttling and Caesars/Teddybears’ Joakim Åhlund started Smile years ago and this track features Lykke Li on vocals 06/22/2024 01:43 PM

DJ: Morgan Title track from the movie of the same name. 24 Hour Party People is a 2002 British biographical comedy drama film about Manchester's popular music community from 1976 to 1992, and specifically about Factory Records. 06/22/2024 01:40 PM

Thunderpussy will be at the beloved, annual Wildrose Pride Festival aka ‘Bush Garden’. Join KEXP LIVE, in-person and on-air for Pride at The Wildrose in Seattle's Capitol Hill neighborhood on Sunday (6/30) from noon to 6 PM Pacific. https://www.kexp.org/pride/ 06/22/2024 01:32 PM

Suki Waterhouse will play the Day in Day Out Festival at Seattle Center on Saturday, July 13th! She'll be at the Warfield Theater in San Francisco on Friday, October 25th. Memoir of a Sparklemuffin will be out in September. https://sukiwaterhouse.bandcamp.com 06/22/2024 01:14 PM

DJ: Morgan Lavender Country was an American country music band formed in 1972 whose self-titled 1973 album is the first known gay-themed album in country music history. Based in Seattle, the band originally consisted of lead singer and guitarist Patrick Haggerty, keyboardist Michael Carr, singer and fiddler Eve Morris and guitarist Robert Hammerstrom. Lavender Country released two studio albums Lavender Country (1973) and Blackberry Rose (2019). 06/22/2024 01:12 PM

DJ: Morgan Shannon and the Clams will be in Seattle performing their new album at the Neptune Wednesday, October 16th! They will also be performing at the Tom Mcall Waterfront in Portland July 27th, and in Oakland at the Fox Theatre on October 19th! https://shannonandtheclams.bandcamp.com 06/22/2024 01:08 PM

DJ: Morgan Golden Brown was the most played song in the UK in 1982. The most popular song in the US that same year? You guessed it, "Physical" by Olivia Newton-John. "Eye of the Tiger" by Survivor came in second followed by Joan Jett with "I Love Rock 'n Roll" which came in third. https://thestranglers.co.uk/ 06/22/2024 01:06 PM

DJ: Morgan This song, written by Rod Argent, has a lot of distinct elements that made it a rock classic and landed The Zombies in the Rock And Roll Hall Of Fame in 2019. For starters, the lead instrument is Rod Argent's electric piano, which was very unusual at the time - in the UK it was the first hit song with that lead instrument. And then there's the breathy vocals of lead singer Colin Blunstone. Check out KEXP's video of The Zombies playing SXSW in 2013: https://bit.ly/3wC0iTH
